It seems like the available data does not provide a definitive ranking of the top 5 fastest animals. However, here is a list of some incredibly fast animals and their respective speeds:

1. Peregrine Falcon: Capable of reaching a speed of 240 mph (386 km/h) during its hunting dive, known as a stoop.
2. White-throated Needletail: This bird can fly at speeds of up to 69 mph (111 km/h), making it one of the fastest in powered flight.
3. Golden Eagle: With a top speed of 150 mph (241 km/h) in horizontal flight, the Golden Eagle is incredibly swift.
4. Pronghorn: Among land mammals, the Pronghorn takes the title of one of the fastest, reaching speeds of 61 mph (98 km/h). 
5. Greyhound: Known for its speed and endurance, the Greyhound dog breed can run at an impressive 45 mph (72 km/h).
